attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies 64 bit metasploit wininet reverse shellcode. May also be used by other malware families.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies the 64 bit API hashing function used by Metasploit. This has been re-used by many other malware families.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a malicious loader or backdoor, likely a Cobalt Strike Beacon or similar shellcode-based implant. It exhibits several high-confidence indicators: 1) Manual symbol resolution by walking the Process Environment Block (PEB) and LDR module list using a ROR13 hashing algorithm to bypass the Import Address Table (IAT). 2) The entry point resides in a Read-Write-Execute (RWX) memory segment (.tsxa). 3) It dynamically loads 'wininet' to perform network communications, using a hardcoded Edge User-Agent and a long, high-entropy URI path (/MtxAb2z5Vr4tPCw-...) typical of C2 traffic. 4) Use of VirtualProtect to manage executable memory regions for payload staging.
